            <bug_when>2009-07-31 11:33:52 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>Following up on bug#2391, I detected that some classes use the same private 
name in both their statics and members section. Among other things, this makes 
it difficult to detect legal use of privates in build versions of applications. 
The offending signatures are:

qx.io.remote.Request: __seqNum

qx.io.remote.transport.Script: __uniqueId

The uniform feedback from the team was that while this might be technically 
possible, it should be considered bad style and should not be present in the 
framework. Is this possible for the listed classes?</thetext>
          </long_desc>
